                            <comment id="12956764" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 19 Sep 2010 13:56:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please take more time to write down details when creating tickets.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Just providing a title is not sufficient to go after.&lt;br/&gt;
More details and source code helps us to go track down what you mean.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12956775" author="di_m_an" created="Sun, 19 Sep 2010 15:09:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Done&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12956790" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 19 Sep 2010 15:13:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What version of Spring are you using as Spring 2.5 and 3.0 is different how Spring does IoC internally which somehow could cause an issue, so its great to know which version of Spring you use.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12956776" author="di_m_an" created="Sun, 19 Sep 2010 15:27:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I use Spring 3.0.3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As far as I could understand, for some reason CXF uses SingletonFactory to get (create) the bean, but should use SpringBeanFactory.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12956774" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 19 Sep 2010 15:30:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have re-produced the issue in an unit test in camel-cxf.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think I have it fixed, but running tests to ensure it wont break stuff.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12956773" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 19 Sep 2010 15:47:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;trunk: 998687.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Feel free to test the fix in your system as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12956772" author="di_m_an" created="Sun, 19 Sep 2010 16:32:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Great! Tested and it works now, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
